The paper discusses the development of an algorithm that facilitates human-machine cooperation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm uses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the role of cultural norms, emotions, and pre-evolved dispositions in facilitating cooperation, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of signaling mechanisms, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and social influence (cs.SI).
